Package nl.naturalis.geneious.name

Class DefaultSequenceInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.geneious.name.SequenceInfo
      • nl.naturalis.geneious.name.DefaultSequenceInfo
  • public class DefaultSequenceInfo
extends SequenceInfo
    A subclass of {link SequenceInfo} exclusively used by the Split Name operation. It works on pre-existing documents, using their name as input for the SequenceNameParser.

      • createNote

        public void createNote()
                throws NotParsableException
        Description copied from class: SequenceInfo
        Creates a NaturalisNote containing the annotations that were parsed out of the sequence name. This method must be called before getNote. Although there is currently no difference between parsing AB1 file names and fasta headers, we don't rely on it, so this method must be implemented by subclasses.
        Specified by:
        createNote in class SequenceInfo
        Throws:
        NotParsableException - If the sequence name did not comply with the rules for naming AB1 or fasta files.
